[4] Brazil (Sao Paulo)
Date: Thu 1 Apr 2010
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/cidades/sp/mat/2010/04/01/sp-registra-queda-nos-casos-de-dengue-em-marco-diz-secretaria-de-saude-916236308.asp>


Dengue cases in the state of Sao Paulo have fallen 52 percent in
March [2010] compared to the previous month. According to the Sao
Paulo state Secretariat of Health, 8076 cases of the disease were
registered in the past month [March 2010] and 16 869 in February
2010. In January 2010, there were 9377 cases.

Ribeirao Preto was the municipality with the greatest number of
cases, followed by Sao Jose do Rio Preto, with 3414, Guaruja, with
2979, Sao Vicente, with 1877 and Aractuba, with 1667.

The Secretariat stated that the rains, together with elevated
temperatures, favored the proliferation of the disease [mosquito
vectors of the virus]. Because of this, he repeated the importance of
help by the population in the control of reproduction of the mosquito vector.

Among the actions carried out by the Secretariat to counter the
advance of the disease are the use of insecticides in 172
municipalities and advice and technical support in another 122 cities.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed-port@promedmail.org>

