[5] Brazil (Ribeirao Preto, SP)
Date: Thu 1 Apr 2010
Source: Ribeirao Preto Online [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.ribeiraopretoonline.com.br/saude/mergulhado-em-uma-epidemia-ribeirao-preto-luta-contra-a-dengue/34928>


On this Thursday [1 Apr 2010], the Secretariat of Health of Ribeirao
Preto released an updated bulletin with the dengue cases in the city.
Living through the worst [dengue] epidemic in its history, the
municipality has now registered 7894 cases in 2010, 1897 more than
the 5997 registered in 2006, then the worst year for the disease. The
month of March 2010 has emerged as the champion for cases in the
history of Ribeirao Preto. With nearly 6000 cases (5932), the 31 days
of the month [of March 2010] overran the [capacity of] basic health
units and caused the population to worry even more about the problem.

According to the Division of Epidemiological Surveillance, the daily
mean number of confirmed cases reached 87.7. The municipal government
continues with various measures to contain the _Aedes aegypti_
mosquito, the vector of the disease [virus]. The greatest [public]
appeal is that people eliminate mosquito breeding sites and observe
sites of [mosquito breeding] risk, especially on rainy days.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed-port@promedmail.org>

[It is a pathetic effort in vain, like wanting to cover the sun with
a sieve, that in regions immersed in major epidemics, such as
Ribeirao Preto and Santos, the health authorities are playing with
words and numbers. Dengue is a serious public health problem in Sao
Paulo and in the rest of the country, and no breakthrough has
occurred with respect to its control, which reminds me of the
economist who drowned in a river whose average depth was 50 cm [17
in]. - Mod.LJS]

