[8] Argentina (Buenos Aires)
Date: Thu 1 Apr 2010
Source: La Republica [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.diariolarepublica.com.ar/notix/noticia.php?i=167229>


In recent hours, the Ministry of Public Health confirmed 4 more cases
with symptoms suspicious [of dengue], and the number at the
provincial level climbed to 21. People with [dengue] symptoms were
detected in different neighborhoods of the capital, where an
[epidemiological] blockade was carried out with corresponding public
awareness campaigns.

Another of the conclusions that could be reached by Public Health
with the new suspicious cases is that the virus that circulates in
the province is [dengue virus] type 1, which is milder [The statement
that the DENV-1 virus currently circulating is less virulent is pure
speculation at this point. - Mod.TY]. Currently, the serological
samples from the potentially infected individuals are being tested at
the Instituto Maiztegui, in Buenos Aires province [The report
indicates that one case is likely imported from Paraguay, but 3
others had no recent travel history.].

Confronting this situation, the Office of the Director of
Epidemiology carried out visits to the homes of the patients to
gather epidemiological data, and to deliver [mosquito] repellents to
the families and alert them to the need to get a medical consultation
early in case of the appearance of symptoms compatible with the
disease. Moreover, fumigation was carried out in their houses and
neighboring homes in a radius of 9 blocks (according to the vector
blockade protocol), [done] together with municipal personnel for each
one of the cases.

Also, searches for febrile individuals were carried out in the entire
health cordoned [area], detecting retrospectively 3 suspected cases,
from which samples were taken in the field for [submission to] the
laboratory. All were negative [for dengue]. During these searches,
activities for [public] awareness and sensitivity about the disease
were carried out by health agents under coordination by CAPS [primary
health care centers] and physicians of the Office of Epidemiology and
family medicine belonging to the Hospital Escuela [Teaching
Hospital]. And an entomological survey was carried out with field
samples taken by municipal sanitary agents.

In the current situation, the circulation of [dengue] virus serotype
1 has been confirmed by the national reference laboratory "Julio
Maiztegui". Up to the present and since the notification of the 1st
case in the San Martin Neighborhood, 21 cases have been registered,
of which 16 are from the capital, 4 from Empedrado and one from
Esquina. Most of the cases are in San Martin.

--
Communicated by:
