[9] Paraguay
Date: Thu 1 Apr 2010
Source: Prensa Latina [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.prensa-latina.cu/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=175340&Itemid=1>


Health authorities in Paraguay are worried about the number of people
with dengue in the country. With this concern, they insist today [1
Apr 2010] on preventive work to avoid this disease [virus] that is
transmitted by the mosquito _Aedes aegypti_. Through some press
media, the Ministry of Public Health and Social Welfare stated the
importance of destroying the breeding sites of this vector.

They are alert about the possible spread of the epidemic after Holy
[Easter] Week, since may people customarily travel from the interior
of the country to the [international] borders and abroad.

Just in the capital, the Hospital Central of the Instituto de
Prevision Social registered more than 340 suspected dengue cases and
79 confirmed [cases].

In respect to this, the Epidemiology Department of the hospital
institution insists that the preventive measures for the disease must
be increased maximally.

In the country, the total number of confirmed dengue cases, from
November of last year [2009] up to March of this year [2010],
increased to 2511.

--
